aristaQosMib.description: ********************************** Overview ********************************** This MIB provides read access to Quality of Service (QoS) configuration and statistics information for Arista platforms. Configuration information available through this MIB includes all class-map, policy-map, and service-policy parameters. The definitions of these object types are given below. Statistics available through this MIB include dropped, sent and matched packet counters per traffic class after any configured QoS policies are applied and per chip ECN counters if supported. ********************************** Definitions ********************************** Class map - A data structure that uses access-control lists to define a data stream. Policy map - A data structure that associates class maps identifying specific data streams with actions that control its transmission. Action - A traffic-management action that is applied to traffic classified as belonging to a particular class. Actions may include modifying CoS or DSCP fields, assigning to traffic-class queues, shaping, or filtering.

AristaQosMapType.name: AristaQosMapType
AristaQosMapType.description: The type of a class or policy map. controlPlane - The map is applicable only on the control plane of the device. dataPlane - The map is applicable only on the data plane of the device.

AristaQosShortId.name: AristaQosShortId
AristaQosShortId.description: Identifier with bounded length, derived from a name that may be longer. It includes the first 30 characters of the name. If the name is longer than 30 characters, the identifier contains a hash of the remaining characters in the name, expressed as decimal digits. For example: - name 'one-two-three': identifier 'one-two-three' - name 'one-two-three-four-five-six-seven': identifier 'one-two-three-four-five-six-se3877954092'

aristaClassMapTable.name: aristaClassMapTable
aristaClassMapTable.description: Lists the class maps configured on the system.

aristaClassMapId.name: aristaClassMapId
aristaClassMapId.description: Bounded-length identifier for a given class map, derived from the class map's name.

aristaClassMapType.name: aristaClassMapType
aristaClassMapType.description: Type of a given class map.

aristaClassMapName.name: aristaClassMapName
aristaClassMapName.description: Name of a given class map.

aristaClassMapMatchCondition.name: aristaClassMapMatchCondition
aristaClassMapMatchCondition.description: Indicates how many match criteria traffic must match in order to belong to a class with multiple match critera.

aristaClassMapMatchTable.name: aristaClassMapMatchTable
aristaClassMapMatchTable.description: Describes the match criteria used to classify traffic as belonging to a class map.

aristaClassMapMatchEntry.name: aristaClassMapMatchEntry
aristaClassMapMatchEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aristaClassMapMatchTable.

aristaClassMapMatchIndex.name: aristaClassMapMatchIndex
aristaClassMapMatchIndex.description: This index identifies the position of a match criterion among all the criteria for a class map.

aristaClassMapMatchType.name: aristaClassMapMatchType
aristaClassMapMatchType.description: Indicates the type of a match criterion for a class map. ipv4AccessGroup(1) means that it is an IPv4 access-control list. ipv6AccessGroup(2) means that it is an IPv6 access-control list. vlan(3) means that it is a VLAN-based match criterion.

aristaClassMapMatchName.name: aristaClassMapMatchName
aristaClassMapMatchName.description: Indicates the name of the access-control list if aristaClassMapMatchType is ipv4AccessGroup(1) or ipv6AccessGroup(2). Otherwise, it indicates the masked VLAN value or the comma-separated list of VLAN range values contained in the match criterion.

aristaPolicyMapTable.name: aristaPolicyMapTable
aristaPolicyMapTable.description: Lists the policy maps configured on the system.

aristaPolicyMapId.name: aristaPolicyMapId
aristaPolicyMapId.description: Bounded-length identifier for a given policy map, derived from the policy map's name.

aristaPolicyMapType.name: aristaPolicyMapType
aristaPolicyMapType.description: Type of a given policy map.

aristaPolicyMapName.name: aristaPolicyMapName
aristaPolicyMapName.description: Name of a given policy map.

aristaPolicyMapClassTable.name: aristaPolicyMapClassTable
aristaPolicyMapClassTable.description: Lists the classes associated with a given policy map.

aristaPolicyMapClassIndex.name: aristaPolicyMapClassIndex
aristaPolicyMapClassIndex.description: Determines the sequence in which traffic is matched to classes within a policy map. The class with the smallest aristaPolicyMapClassIndex is given the first preference. Class Index values may not be consecutive.

aristaPolicyMapClassId.name: aristaPolicyMapClassId
aristaPolicyMapClassId.description: Identifier of the class map for a given class in a policy map.

aristaPolicyMapActionTable.name: aristaPolicyMapActionTable
aristaPolicyMapActionTable.description: Lists the actions that are applied to traffic classified as belonging to a particular class in a policy map.

aristaPolicyMapActionEntry.name: aristaPolicyMapActionEntry
aristaPolicyMapActionEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aristaPolicyMapActionTable.

aristaPolicyMapActionType.name: aristaPolicyMapActionType
aristaPolicyMapActionType.description: Type of a traffic-management action. For example: If the action is 'set cos 5', then the action type is 'actionSetCos'.

aristaPolicyMapActionRateUnit.name: aristaPolicyMapActionRateUnit
aristaPolicyMapActionRateUnit.description: Indicates the rate unit of shaping/bandwidth actions. rateUnitNone - This action is not a shaping or bandwidth action. rateUnitPps - Packets per second rateUnitKbps - Kilobits per second

aristaPolicyMapActionValue.name: aristaPolicyMapActionValue
aristaPolicyMapActionValue.description: Value applied in a traffic-management action. For example: If the action is 'set cos 5', then aristaPolicyMapActionValue is 5.

aristaServicePolicyTable.name: aristaServicePolicyTable
aristaServicePolicyTable.description: Lists the policy maps currently applied to interfaces.

aristaServicePolicyEntry.name: aristaServicePolicyEntry
aristaServicePolicyEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aristaServicePolicyTable.

aristaServicePolicyIfIndex.name: aristaServicePolicyIfIndex
aristaServicePolicyIfIndex.description: The index of interface to which a policy map is applied.

aristaServicePolicyDirection.name: aristaServicePolicyDirection
aristaServicePolicyDirection.description: The direction of traffic for which the service policy applies. input - The service policy applies to inbound traffic. output - The service policy applies to outbound traffic.

aristaServicePolicyMapId.name: aristaServicePolicyMapId
aristaServicePolicyMapId.description: Identifier of the policy map applied to the interface.

aristaServicePolicyMapType.name: aristaServicePolicyMapType
aristaServicePolicyMapType.description: Type of the policy map applied to the interface.

aristaQosStatsTable.name: aristaQosStatsTable
aristaQosStatsTable.description: An entry in this table contains dropped, sent and matched packet counters for a given class of a policy map applied in a given direction. Counts are aggregated for all interfaces.

aristaQosStatsEntry.name: aristaQosStatsEntry
aristaQosStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aristaQosStatsTable.

aristaQosPktsDropped.name: aristaQosPktsDropped
aristaQosPktsDropped.description: The number of packets dropped by a service policy. This number is zero for classes of type dataPlane.

aristaQosPktsSent.name: aristaQosPktsSent
aristaQosPktsSent.description: The number of packets classified by a service policy and allowed through.

aristaQosPktsMatched.name: aristaQosPktsMatched
aristaQosPktsMatched.description: The number of packets classified by a service policy. Equal to the sum of aristaQosPktsDropped and aristaQosPktsSent.

aristaEcnCounterTable.name: aristaEcnCounterTable
aristaEcnCounterTable.description: Lists the ECN Counter Value per unit as supported. Since different Arista devices have different capabilities for ECN counters, the table would contain the counter information per entity. This includes both packets that were received with congestion marked (ECN bits set) as well as packets that this Arista device marked with ECN bits before transmission. In cases where the platform is unable to count the already marked packets, the counter will only reflect the ones being marked by this specific device on the transmit side.

aristaEcnCounterEntry.name: aristaEcnCounterEntry
aristaEcnCounterEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aristaEcnCounterTable.

aristaEcnCounterDescriptor.name: aristaEcnCounterDescriptor
aristaEcnCounterDescriptor.description: Describes the entity that the counter corresponds to. For instance, devices supporting ECN counters per forwarding element (or per chip) will have descriptor containing information like <ChipName>

aristaEcnCounterValue.name: aristaEcnCounterValue
aristaEcnCounterValue.description: The number of packets above average threshhold

aristaEcnCounterEntity.name: aristaEcnCounterEntity
aristaEcnCounterEntity.description: The physical index corresponding to the entity which is a non zero value used to identify a physical entity. This value will be zero if the entity does not have a physical index

aristaQosMibCompliance.name: aristaQosMibCompliance
aristaQosMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for Arista switches that support ARISTA-QOS-MIB.

aristaClassMapGroup.name: aristaClassMapGroup
aristaClassMapGroup.description: The collection of objects that represent QoS configuration and statistics information for class maps.

aristaPolicyMapGroup.name: aristaPolicyMapGroup
aristaPolicyMapGroup.description: The collection of objects that represent QoS configuration information for policy maps.

aristaPolicyMapActionGroup.name: aristaPolicyMapActionGroup
aristaPolicyMapActionGroup.description: The collection of objects that represent configuration information for QoS actions.

aristaServicePolicyGroup.name: aristaServicePolicyGroup
aristaServicePolicyGroup.description: The collection of objects that represent QoS configuration information for service policies.

aristaEcnCounterGroup.name: aristaEcnCounterGroup
aristaEcnCounterGroup.description: The objects that represent ECN counter information
